<div type="apparatus"><head>Apparatus</head><p>Cormack saw the trace of an upright in l. 1, and so read <foreign lang="grc"><supplied reason="lost">ἐ</supplied>τ<supplied reason="lost">είμησεν</supplied></foreign>; but this might be a trace left by the moulding.</p></div><div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p><gap reason="lost" dim="left"/> <supplied reason="lost" cert="low">honoured</supplied> Chaireas the stephanephoros.</p>
</div>

<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>There may have been a verb of honouring on an upper feature; but the two texts, <xref type="inscription" n="1004" href="120602">12.602</xref> and <xref type="inscription" n="1005" href="110409">11.409</xref> (= MAMA 466, 467), both very similar, may perhaps be complete.</p>
</div>

